      "text": "Captain, [REDACTED] with residence at [REDACTED] Tacoma, Washington,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "Primary MOS 1051 and 1058. In 1942 he was with the Criminal Investigation Division, b6",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "State of Washington, and previously had been an oil technician with the Union Pacific",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Railway. [REDACTED] entered the service in 1942 as an enlisted man and served as such",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "for seventeen months. In 1943 he was commissioned on graduation from flying school",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "and served a total of twenty-nine months. A check of the Tacoma city directory was",
      "status": "image_matched"
